  "display_name": "Experimental Behavioral Economics Studies",
  "description": "This cluster of papers explores the role of social preferences in economic behavior through a wide range of experimental studies. It investigates topics such as reciprocity, cooperation, incentives, gender differences, trust, fairness, altruism, and competition. The research delves into the psychological and behavioral aspects that influence decision-making in economic contexts.",
